title: For Sale:  Great Western Arms Co. (Not Colt) Sold pending arrival of funds
postcontent: Here I have an original Great Western Arms Co. single action .22. These are not to be confused with the Pietta Great Western II. Great Western Arms Co. started around 1953 and only lasted about 10 years, producing just over 22,000 revolvers during the time that Colt quit producing the Single Action Army. This revolver is full sized, not a scaled down single action. 100% engraved with COA on the engraving, with stag grips. The action is smooth as glass. These revolvers were built from Colt specs. and the parts are Colt 1st and early 2nd generation interchangeable. These essentially are Colt guns without the Colt name. The cylinder stop, hand, cylinder, screws, bushing, etc. are all Colt interchangeable. John Wayne used a matched pair of Great Westerns in his last movie, The Shootist. They were not Colts. If interested, email me with your phone number and I will call you back. If you want it shipped, it will cost at least an extra $80.00 for overnight shipping to your FFL.

title: For Sale:  Ghost munitions: rotary tumblers
postcontent:
Hello everyone from ghost munitions I'd like to introduce our latest product to the ghost munitions line of brass and cleaning solutions. 

We are now manufacturing rotary tumblers for home reloaders and commercial companies alike. Here are the specs for our offerings 

We start out with an all steel frame welded together by hand right here in America. marathon county WI to be exact utilizing the best and as many made in America products as we can we assemble our tumblers in house. 

What about capacity? 

This is where YOU the customer has to do a little leg work.  We want to provide the most efficient tumblers we can not only with low energy motors and water sensible cleaning but we want to provide a product that fits you. Normally we use a tank constructed by hand from American made pvc. For our commercial guys these tanks are 8" in diameter and approximately 22" long giving you the flexibly to run 500 pcs of 9mm to 1500 cases of 5.56 brass. If you are just a hobbyist we also have you in mind we can customize a tank that best fits you for both production and space. These are not made in China machines that will break after a week and anyone that's used or seen a cement mixer for using stainless steel media knows they are loud and inefficient.  

We can make tanks from 6" x 10" to 8"x24" one thing to consider is weight. Utilizing about 4 gallons of water and approximately 30 pounds of pellet pins a full large tank can be as much at 80# not a problem for some but not everyone needs that kind of capacity. 

So what all do I get? 

Tumblers will ship fully assembled ready to use. All you'll need to do is fill your tank with brass and media a little dawn some lemi shine top it off with warm tap water and away you go. 

What about shipping? 

These bad boys are not light weighting in at approximately 75# or a hair over we would like to ship these as best we can for the most cost effective rates if you are located in Wi we would be more than happy to have you by the shop to pick yours up or we can deliver for fuel cost. Nationwide we will acquire a shipping quote before an order is finalized. 

How about price? 

Pricing is going to be $450 for our large tumbler and smaller tumblers will be slightly less. All tumblers are custom built by hand so no worries about "out of stock on that model but we have this one right here for a little more." That's not how we believe customers should be treated. 

If interested we would love to hear from you. 

We accept money orders, checks, PayPal and major credit cards processed via intuit go payments. 

Stand by for pictures coming soon 

Thanks and keep your head down. Ghost Munitions team

Since chrome lining may slightly affect accuracy, and since most AR-15 rifles are designed with accuracy as a benchmark, 
and since virtually all .223 / 5.56 Nato is non corrosive...most AR manufacturers do not chrome line barrels.
